close_reason: Repo quality is ratcheted to 100% docstrings and 100/100/100/100 tests with zero duplication and exact suppression budgets.
body: "## Evidence (review pass 2026-07-13, gate-verified)\n\nRunning `node scripts/release/static-quality-gate.mjs` with DEFAULT thresholds (100%) fails on exactly two files, both introduced by PR#536 (governance-audit extraction phase 2):\n\n- `packages/pm-governance-audit/extensions/governance-audit/runtime-utils.ts` — missing module docstring, 13 exported docstrings, 5 member docstrings (LinkedArtifactAuditPayload/LinkedArtifactAuditEntry fields).\n- `packages/pm-governance-audit/extensions/governance-audit/sdk.ts` — missing module docstring + 2 exported docstrings (line 26 exported value, RuntimeStatusRegistry line 50).\n\nAchieved coverage today: source 99.29%, exported 99.41%, member 99.89%. The repo previously reached literal 100% via the closed docstring waves (pm-4ak1 repo-wide, pm-qely packages/*). CI stays green because `quality:static` in package.json passes floors `--min-docstring-coverage 92.93 --min-exported-docstring-coverage 84.41 --min-member-docstring-coverage 13.655` — set before the waves completed and never ratcheted, so ~6-15 points of headroom silently absorb regressions. Ratcheting the floors is the control that makes the next extraction-style PR fail instead of drift.\n\n## Dead export (same files, same fix window)\n\n`DEFAULT_CLOSURE_LIKE_METADATA_FIELD_PATTERNS` (runtime-utils.ts:3) has ZERO call sites across src/, tests/, packages/, scripts/ — including inside runtime-utils.ts itself. normalize.ts derives its closure-like patterns from `settings.validation.lifecycle_closure_like_*_patterns` (normalize.ts:202-208), so the constant is an extraction leftover default table nobody reads. Contrast: `buildLinkedArtifactAudit` LOOKS test-only from an external grep but is called internally at runtime-utils.ts:166 and powers the shipped `pm files/docs --audit` flag (verified live) — do NOT remove it.\n\nNot covered by: pm-u5zr (windows spec exemption), pm-rxp1 CLOSED (boundary spec), pm-j8z6 (file links), pm-92if (CodeFactor-scoped)."
